events.name: Clemson Tigers at Florida State Seminoles

headlines.description: With Heisman Trophy winner Jameis Winston watching from the sideline, No. 1 Florida State come back to beat No. 22 Clemson 23-17 in overtime on Karlos Williams' 12-yard touchdown run Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 1 FSU dodges Clemson in OT

events.name: Oregon Ducks at Washington State Cougars

headlines.description: Marcus Mariota threw for 329 yards and five touchdowns as No. 2 Oregon held off Washington State 38-31 on Saturday night in a matchup of two of the top offenses in the nation.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mariota's 5 TDs lift Ducks

events.name: Florida Gators at Alabama Crimson Tide

headlines.description: Blake Sims recorded Alabama's second-best passing day with 445 yards and the third-ranked Crimson Tide overcame a sloppy performance to beat Florida 42-21 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cooper, Sims help Tide roll Gators

events.name: Oklahoma Sooners at West Virginia Mountaineers

headlines.description: Bruising freshman Samaje Perine rushed for 242 yards and four touchdowns to lead No. 4 Oklahoma to a 45-33 win over West Virginia in their Big 12 opener Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Perine's 242, 4 TDs get OU by WVU

events.name: Texas A&M Aggies at SMU Mustangs

headlines.description: Kenny Hill had 322 yards of total offense playing only the first half, Jeremy Tabuyo turned two short passes into touchdowns and sixth-ranked Texas A&M rolled to a 58-6 victory Saturday at SMU.
headlines.shortLinkText: Aggies blast SMU for 1st 4-0 start since 2006

events.name: Mississippi State Bulldogs at LSU Tigers

headlines.description: Dak Prescott highlighted a dynamic performance with two touchdown passes and 56-yard scoring run, and Mississippi State held off a wild rally by No. 8 LSU for a 34-29 victory Saturday night that snapped the Bulldogs' 14-year losing streak in the series.
headlines.shortLinkText: Miss. St. hangs on, shocks No. 8 LSU

events.name: Eastern Michigan Eagles at Michigan State Spartans

headlines.description: Connor Cook threw two touchdown passes and ran for a score as No. 11 Michigan State scored the third-most points in program history, smashing Eastern Michigan 73-14 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 11 MSU scores 73 in rout of E. Michigan

events.name: Troy Trojans at Georgia Bulldogs

headlines.description: Sony Michel ran for 155 yards and three touchdowns to highlight a big day for freshmen in No. 13 Georgia's 66-0 win over Troy on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Georgia posts most lopsided win since 1958
